The paper deals with the problem of designing a neural network architecture for the control of LTI systems, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for generating ReLU NN architectures, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed algorithm to robotics (cs.RO), which is a specific area of control systems and machine learning.
